# AudioVolumeSystem

## Purpose
Owns the live audio volumes. On the first frame the `EngineConfigSingletonComponent` is present, it
creates `AudioVolumeSingletonComponent` initialised from the config's master/sound/music volumes.
Thereafter it applies `SetAudioVolumeRequestOneFrameComponent` requests (the App's runtime volume
changes) into that singleton. Returns early while the engine config is absent.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Source of the initial master/sound/music volumes |
| SetAudioVolumeRequestOneFrameComponent | read | App request carrying the desired master/sound/music volumes |
| AudioVolumeSingletonComponent | write | Presence-check; created lazily once config exists, then updated in place |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| AudioVolumeSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once from config; updated in place by volume requests |
